# deals/_fleet/queue.txt — fleet-run input source.
#
# One slug per line. Blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored.
# Slugs are kebab-case (lowercase, digits, hyphens) and must NOT start with an
# underscore — that prefix is reserved for fleet/system directories.
#
# This file is read by `dudu:fleet-run` only when neither `--slugs` nor
# `--auto` is passed. `--slugs` and `--auto` always take priority.
#
# To use: copy this file to deals/_fleet/queue.txt and add one slug per line.

